PIPING MUST BE SYMMETRICAL FOR THE FOLLOWING (SEEDETAIL "A")
A) RISERS FROM REACTOR TO STEAM DRUM
B) DOWNCOMERS FROM STEAM DRUM TO REACTOR
C) REACTOR TUBESHEET VENT LINES TO VENT HDR.
RISERS, DOWNCOMERS AND VENT LINES TO BE PER ASME-A-106 GR B . \nTHICKNESS TO BE CONSISTENT WITH REACTOR AND GAS COOLER \nNOZZLES; RISERS TO HAVE A MINIMUM OF 30° SLOPE.
2" VENT LINES TO RUN SEPARATELY AND TIE-IN TO TWO 6" HEADERS,\n LOCATED AS CLOSE AS POSSIBLE TO THE STEAM DRUM NOZZLE \n(SYMMETRICAL). VENT LINES TO HAVE A MINIMUM OF 30° SLOPE.

INSTALL TRAPS AT
A) ALL LOW POINTS ON STEAM SUPPLY LINE.
B) ALL LOW POINTS UPSTREAM OF STEAM CONTROL VALVE HV-1101, 
 PV-1101 
C) AT ALL LOW POINTS UPSTREAM AND DOWNSTREAM OF STEAM 
 CONTROL VALVE, FV-1107,
BLOWDOWN LINES ENTERING COMMON HEADER TO BE AT 45° IN \nTHE DIRECTION OF FLOW.
CHECK VALVE SHALL NOT BE INSTALLED AT P-110 DISCHARGE LINE.\nTO KEEP THE PUMP WARM WHEN P-110 IS NOT IN OPERATION.
PROVIDE THE MINIMUM STRAIGHT LENGTH OF 5 TIMES THE FULL PIPE\n DIAMETER OR 500 mm, WHICH EVER IS LARGER BEFORE FIRST ELBOW.
PRESSURE GAUGE TO BE VISIBLE FROM STEAM BLOCK AND VENT VALVES.
LEVEL INSTRUMENTS USED FOR INTERLOCK TRIP AND REDUNDANT \nINDICATION MUST SPAN THE ENTIRE DIAMETER OF THE DRUM.
EMERGENCY INSTRUMENT AIR BOTTLE BY CONTROL VALVE\nVENDOR. PROVIDE 20 MINUTE BACKUP AIR SUPPLY.
THREE RELIEF VALVES, EACH SIZED FOR 33.33% OF THE RELIEVING\nCAPACITY BASED ON BURNDOWN CASE AT EOR CONDITIONS.\nMULTIPLE PSV'S CAN BE USED IF PSV SIZE IS TOO BIG.
LINE TO BE PROPERLY SUPPORTED FOR HIGH VIBRATION.
VALVE CONNECTIONS TO STANDPIPE TO BE WELDED.
LG/LT ISOLATION BLOCK VALVES TO BE WELDED TO PIPING.
OH = CONTROLLER OUTPUT HIGH; OL = OUTPUT LOW
DH = HIGH DEVIATION FROM SET POINT; DL = LOW DEVIATION.
INSTRUMENT USED FOR LEVEL CONTROL AND REDUNDANT INDICATION\nSHALL SPAN 0% AT LLL AND 100% AT HLL.
